data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Dimension Transfer
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for a Trainer card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Suspicious Beam β
attacks.text: If Porygon-Z has no Rainbow Energy attached to it, Porygon-Z does 20 damage to itself and Porygon-Z is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error…

data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Conversion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a basic Energy card from your hand. Porygon-Z is the same type as that Energy Card until the end of your turn. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Tri Attack
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 damage times the number of heads.

data.flavorText: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

abilities.name: Dowsing Code
abilities.text: Once during your turn, when you put Porygon-Z G from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your discard pile for up to 2 Pokémon Tool cards, show them to your opponent, and shuffle them into your deck.

attacks.name: Ambush
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage plus 40 more damage.

abilities.name: Install
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), move a Technical Machine card attached to 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

attacks.name: Learning
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon LV.X that levels up from 1 of your Pokémon, and put it onto that Pokémon. (This counts as leveling up that Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Overload
attacks.text: Does 40 damage plus 20 more damage for each Technical Machine card attached to Porygon-Z.

data.name: Porygon-Z

attacks.name: Cyber Crush
attacks.text: Discard all Special Energy attached to each of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Slowing Beam
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless more.

data.flavorText: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error…

ancientTrait.name: θ Stop
ancientTrait.text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's Pokémon's Abilities done to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Digital Reboot
attacks.text: Devolve as many of your Benched Pokémon as many times as you like. Put each Evolution card removed this way into your hand.

attacks.name: Dazzle Blast
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error…

data.name: Porygon-Z LV.X
rules: Put this card onto your Active Porygon-Z. Porygon-Z LV.X can use any attack, Poké-Power, or Poké-Body from its previous level.

abilities.name: Mode Crash
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Porygon-Z LV.X from your hand onto your Active Porygon-Z, you may discard all of your opponent's Special Energy cards in play.

abilities.name: Decode
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for up to any 2 cards and shuffle your deck afterward. Then, put those cards on top of your deck in any order. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.

data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Initialize
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may devolve each of your opponent's evolved Pokémon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Zap Cannon
attacks.text: This Pokémon can't use Zap Cannon during your next turn.

data.flavorText: In order to create a more advanced Pokémon, an additional program was installed, but apparently it contained a defect that makes it move oddly.

data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Crazy Code
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may attach a Special Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tantrum
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: Its behavior is noticeably unstable, which is apparently due to the incompetence of the engineer who updated its programming.

data.name: Porygon-Z-GX
rules: Pokémon-GX rule: When your Pokémon-GX is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Troubleshooting
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Special Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, heal 80 damage from it.

attacks.name: Abnormal Overheating
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Critical Error-GX
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 10 cards and discard them. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Bug Transmission
abilities.text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon during your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Confused.

attacks.name: Superbeam
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: A faulty update was added to its programming. Its behavior is noticeably strange, so the experiment may have been a failure.

data.name: Porygon-Z

attacks.name: Downgrading Beam
attacks.text: Devolve 1 of your opponent's evolved Pokémon by removing any number of Evolution cards from it. Your opponent shuffles those cards into their deck.

data.flavorText: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.

data.name: Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Buggy Turbo
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may flip a coin. If heads, attach up to 4 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon. If tails, discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Energized Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: Some say an additional program made this Pokémon evolve, but even academics can't agree on whether Porygon-Z is really an evolution.

data.name: Team Rocket's Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Reconstitute
abilities.text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.

attacks.name: R Command
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name in your discard pile.

data.flavorText: An additional program was installed to create a more advanced Pokémon, but it was apparently flawed. Porygon-Z moves oddly as a result.
